	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>397 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Greetings Mr. GEAR Sux&nbsp;&nbsp;:)<br><br>Keep in mind you are only level 8, therefore your gear is about what it should be. At level 8, I would focus on trying to get a better weapon, instead of better armor. It will all come in time. At your level there are no real shortcuts short of outside help (power leveling, twinking, guild twinking, etc.) but there is hope. <br><br>If you think Crushbone is annoying you are missing out on a great zone in my opinion, but I'm sure it's not for everybody and Crushbone is a bit over your head without a group at level 8. Perhaps you will like the zone better at level 12 or so where you don't have to run in fear of the Legos.  Believe me, I ran from thousands of them!<br>What's nice about Crushbone is the fact that you not only get XP for the kill, you also get the Cent belts and the Lego Shoulder Pads that you can turn in to Canloe Nusback in the warriors guild for experience and more items that can be sold, etc. Hopefully you know all about this, but just in case you don't, I thought I'd post it. I turned in Shoulder pads until I was level 20 and still got XP that was measurable.<br><br>You can still hunt in and around the X-roads in BB for many levels to come. Go over towards the docks and check out what mobs you see there. If you have a good group, go check out Chessboard or fight any of the Goblin spawns and camps, not to mention the Bandits that spawn there in BB.  Take on a few Krag Elders. Lots to fight at level 8 and it's all close by. There's really no need to venture out too far unless you just feel like. <br><br>Good luck Brother!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>45th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</p>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr>
